<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ideffdb13a-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7109"><num value="7109">§ 7109.</num><heading> Administrative provisions</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffdb13b-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7109/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Construction</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter preempts or supersedes any other program relating to sheep promotion, research, or information organized and operated under the laws of the United States or any State.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="ideffdb13c-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s7109/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Amendments to orders</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The provisions of this chapter applicable to an order shall be applicable to amendments to the order, except that the Secretary is not required to conduct a referendum on a proposed amendment to an order.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="ideffdb13d-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/407/s10">Pub. L. 103–407, § 10</ref>, <date date="1994-10-22">Oct. 22, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/4226">108 Stat. 4226</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
